#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:664
#, no-c-format
msgid "Par:"
msgstr "Par:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:666
#, no-c-format
msgid "The par of the hole."
msgstr "Par rupe:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:669
#, no-c-format
msgid "Maximum:"
msgstr "Maksimum:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:671
#, no-c-format
msgid "The maximum number of strokes a player can take on the hole."
msgstr "Maksimalni broj udaraca koji igrač može uputiti ka rupi."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show border walls"
msgstr "Prikaži rubne zidove"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:676
#, no-c-format
msgid "Whether or not to show walls around the border of the hole."
msgstr "Da li će biti prikazani zidovi oko ruba rube."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:685
#, no-c-format
msgid "Type"
msgstr "Tip:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:687
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose the type of the slope - <guilabel>Vertical</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Horizontal</guilabel>, <guilabel>Diagonal</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Opposite Diagonal</guilabel>, <guilabel>Circular</guilabel>. "
"Diagonal and opposite diagonal slopes are triangles, while circular slopes "
"are circles. Vertical and horizontal slopes are rectangles of course."
msgstr ""
"Odaberite vrstu padine - <guilabel>Vertikalna</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Horizontalna</guilabel>, <guilabel>Dijagonalna</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Obrnuto Dijagonalna</guilabel>, <guilabel>Cirkularna</guilabel>. "
"Dijagonalne i obrnuto dijagonale padine su trouglovi, dok su cirkularne "
"padine krugovi. Vertikalne i horizontalne padine su u obliku pravougaonika, "
"naravno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:690
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reverse direction"
msgstr "Obrnuti smjer"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:692
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether or not to reverse the slant of the slope. For example, consider an "
"elliptical slope (a circular slope). When it is not reversed, it pushes "
"balls outward like a mound. When it is reversed, it sucks balls inward like "
"a hole."
msgstr ""
"Da li će pravac u kojem padina gura lopticu biti obrnut. Naprimjer, "
"posmatrajmo eliptičnu padinu (kružna padina). Kada nije obrnuta, gura "
"lopticu napolje kao brežuljak. Kada je obrnuta, usisava lopticu unutra kao "
"rupa."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:695
#, no-c-format
msgid "Unmovable"
msgstr "Nepokretno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:697
#, no-c-format
msgid "Whether or not this can be moved by other objects, like floaters."
msgstr ""
"Može li ili ne ovo biti pokrenuto od strane drugih predmeta, kao što su "
"plutajuće platforme."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:699
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If a floater overlaps with this object at any point on this path, and the "
#| "slope is large and thus won't move the floater, you <emphasis>must</"
#| "emphasis> make the slope <guilabel>Unmovable</guilabel>, or &kappname; "
#| "will suffer poor performance!"
msgid ""
"If a floater overlaps with this object at any point on this path, and the "
"slope is large and thus won't move the floater, you <emphasis>must</"
"emphasis> make the slope <guilabel>Unmovable</guilabel>, or &kolf; will "
"suffer poor performance!"
msgstr ""
"Ako se plutajuća platforma preklapa sa ovim predmetom na ovoj putanji, a "
"padina je velika, i stoga neće pomjerati platformu,  <emphasis>morate</"
"emphasis> učiniti padinu <guilabel>Nepomičnom</guilabel>, ili će &kappname; "
"trpiti loše performanse."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:703
#, no-c-format
msgid "Grade:"
msgstr "Ocjena:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:705
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose the grade (steepness) of the slope by moving the slider so the grade "
"moves towards 0 or 8, where 8 is steepest and 0 is flat. Steeper slopes push "
"the ball more."
msgstr ""
"Odaberite ocjenu(nagetost) padine pomjeranjem klizača tako da se ocjena "
"pomjera prema 0 ili prema 8, gdje je 8 najstrmije a 0 potpuno ravno. Padine "
"sa većom nagetošću više guraju lopticu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:712
#, no-c-format
msgid "Puddles and Sand have the same configuration options as each other."
msgstr "Bare i pijesak imaju iste konfiguracijske opcije."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:715
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable show/hide"
msgstr "Aktiviraj prikaži/sakrij"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:717
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checking this enables the flashing of this puddle or sand."
msgstr "Ako je ovo zakačeno, uključeno je bljeskanje ove bare ili pijeska."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:724
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The more towards <guilabel>Fast</guilabel> the slider is, the faster the "
"puddle or sand flashes."
msgstr ""
"Što je klizač više pomjeren prema <guilabel>Brzo</guilabel>, to će bara ili "
"pijesak brže bljeskati."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:730
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bridges, Windmills, Floaters, and Signs"
msgstr "Mostovi, vjetrenjače, plutajuće platforme i znakovi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:731
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bridges, windmills, floaters, and signs all have similar settings for "
"configuring on which sides there are border walls. To show the wall on a "
"side, check the check box for that side."
msgstr ""
"Mostovi, vjetrenjače, plutajuće platforme i znakovi imaju slične postavke "
"koje mogu konfigurisati sa kojih strana se nalaze granični zidovi. Da biste "
"prikazli zid na jednoj od strana, zakačite kontrolni okvir za tu stranu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:732
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are also some more specific options for windmills, floaters, and signs."
msgstr ""
"Postoje još neke specifične opcije za vjetrenjače, platforme i  znakove."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:736
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Windmill on bottom"
msgid "Windmill on top"
msgstr "Vjetrenjača na dnu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:738
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Whether or not the black windmill arm is on bottom or top - the default "
#| "is that it is on the bottom. The two half-walls will always be with the "
#| "arm. Note that you cannot enable a border wall on the side that the arm "
#| "is."
msgid ""
"Whether or not the black windmill arm is on bottom or top - the default is "
"that it is on the top. The two half-walls will always be with the arm. Note "
"that you cannot enable a border wall on the side that the arm is."
msgstr ""
"Bilo da se crni dio vjetranječe nalazi na dnu, ili na vrhu, unaprijed je "
"postavljeno da se nalazi na dnu. Dva polu-zida će uvijek biti sa crnim "
"dijelom. Imajte na umu da možete aktivirati granični zid na strani gdje se "
"nalazi crni dio."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:741
#, no-c-format
msgid "Speed"
msgstr "Brzina"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:743
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The more towards <guilabel>Fast</guilabel> the slider is, the faster the "
"black windmill arm moves."
msgstr ""
"Što je klizač više pomjeren prema <guilabel>Brzo</guilabel>, to će se crni "
"dio vjetrenjače brže kretati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:750
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The path the floater moves along is shown by the wall it's connected to."
msgstr "Put kojim se platforma kreće je prikazan zidom na koji je zakačena."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:752
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving speed"
msgstr "Brzina pomjeranja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:754
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The more towards <guilabel>Fast</guilabel> the slider is, the faster the "
"floater moves. If the slider is all the way at the <guilabel>Slow</guilabel> "
"end, the floater will stop."
msgstr ""
"Što je klizač više pomjeren prema <guilabel>Brzo</guilabel>, to se platforma "
"brže kreće. Ako je klizač skroz na kraju <guilabel>Sporo</guilabel> end, "
"platforma će se zaustaviti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:760
#, no-c-format
msgid "Signs"
msgstr "Znakovi"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:762
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sign HTML:"
msgstr "Potpiši HTML:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:764
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can enter any valid &HTML; here. For example, entering <userinput>Hit it "
"&lt;i&gt;softly&lt;/i&gt; towards the slope!</userinput> will create the "
"text <quote>Hit it <emphasis>softly</emphasis> towards the slope!</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Ovdje možete unijeti bilo koji validan &HTML;. Naprimjer, unos "
"<userinput>Udari je &lt;i&gt;lagano&lt;/i&gt; prema padini!</userinput> će "
"kreirati tekst <quote>Udari je <emphasis>lagano</emphasis> prema padini!</"
"quote>."

